summary: This appears to be a cover sheet or metadata record from the FBI's document release, indicating that certain items (photographs, documents, media) were digitized in April 2018. The text is largely administrative and contains scanning notations and item identifiers.

events.title: Digitization of Evidence
events.description: Documents and photographs related to the Epstein case were digitized by the FBI. Negatives and/or original media were not captured in this process.

keyFacts: This document is an administrative cover sheet from the FBI's release of Epstein-related materials.
It indicates that documents and photographs were digitized in April 2018, but original negatives/media were not captured.
The document contains multiple item identifiers (EFTA00007735 through EFTA00007740) suggesting it is part of a larger set of records.
The text includes scanning notations and references to VHS media, indicating some evidence may have been in video format.
